Description: RDIconnect has built its reputation on a patented Dynamic Intelligence Learning and Development curriculum called RDI (Relationship,
Headquarters Regions: Greater Houston Area, Southern US
Full Description: RDIconnect has built its reputation on a patented "Dynamic Intelligence Learning and Development" curriculum called RDI (Relationship, Development and Intervention), which has been successfully tested and utilized in treating families who have children with Asperger's Disease or Autism. By certifying RDI consultants worldwide in it's own certification program, RDIconnect has built a network of managed consultants in over 20 different countries that practice RDI with families in their local region.  RDI Consultants and families who wish to participate in RDI, can now do so through the use of RDIconnect's online web-based application, called RDIos. RDIos includes the RDI curriculum embedded into the application which allows RDI Consultants to track development and learning progress, communicate and collaborate on new methods of progress and research and allow the community to grow more knowledgeable, thus enriching families lives globally. RDIos provides video-sharing between parents and their assigned RDI Consultant that allow for revolutionary assessment and treatment methods unique to the traditional brick-n-mortar clinical office visit. The Internet now gives families the ability to form the same relationship with a clinician via the web, as if the clinician were in an office just down the road.  RDIconnect's next steps are to pilot RDIos in a school setting in LA, adding a team communication concept with Teachers, Consultants and families to utilize the same RDI principles and track progress with children, while they are at home and at school, thus getting everyone involved in the child's devlopment.  Finally, RDIconnect plans is currently working on new add-in modules to RDIos that will allow it to reach other markets that our RDI curriculum would apply to, for example ADD, OCD, Addictions, etc...

Description: Power Liens is the largest directory of physicians working on liens.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Our goal with Power Liens was to improve an attorney’s access to physicians that work on lien.  Two things were necessary to accomplish this mission.  The first was having industry expertise from the perspective of a personal injury attorney to build the best directory.  The second was to leverage the power of technology to create a simple and seamless solution for attorneys, their staff and doctors.    As a practicing attorney, who has also received recognition as a Rising Star Super Lawyer in California, I realized time and again that there was no easy way for me or my colleagues to find doctors that worked on liens.  Besides Chiropractors, there was absolutely no practical way to find any other medical specialties on lien throughout the state.   Power Liens was born out of a desire to address this very need.  Today, less than two years later, there continues to be tremendous demand for our services by attorneys and their staff.  What previously took hours to complete, is now facilitated through our directory in a matter of minutes.  We now enjoy a loyal and highly satisfied customer base, and some of our users have even coined their own slogan for our Company – “created by an attorney for attorneys”.   Our success would not be possible without our dedication to our clients (screened and quality rated health care providers), who in turn provide exceptional service to their patients.  Power Liens currently operates in four states: California, Arizona, Florida and Illinois.  We are well poised for expansion to 10 states by 2015.

Description: Aire Ancient Baths is a hidden gem located in the heart of Manhattan.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The AIRE Group was born 15 years ago in Seville. It was the result of the dream of a group of investors and friends who decided to recuperate the ancient Greek and Roman bath tradition and revive this concept in restored historic buildings. AIRE creates spaces and experiences to relax the body and mind according to ancient traditions of water with temperature contrasts as elements of relaxation and health. Aire de Seville was the first center and it was opened on the street called “AIR”, which gave the name to the whole business group. It is situated in an old mansion from the sixteenth century that a wealthy “Indiano”- the name for the men who made wealth in the Indies- built on the foundations of a Roman ruin from the first century AD (now where Flotarium is located) The building was completely rehabilitated to house the baths. After Seville, in 2008 Aire de Barcelona was inaugurated. This time the Baths were located in a former meat storage area of El Born Market where century old wells that had supplied the city with water were found. Under the brick vaults the Baths were situated in a careful process of the building restoration. The third AIRE arrived in Almería in 2011, this time in the Old Town Square in the center of the city. The bath has its own boutique hotel. The last center is in New York, a textile factory in TriBeCa, Manhattan. This building built in 1883 opened its doors in 2012 to Aire Ancient Baths New York. Each AIRE is unique, located in an old building full of history and personality, but all of them share the quest to create a space for relaxation, full of calm and serenity in an experience for the senses.

Description: Resolve cross-device consumer identities and maximize the value of enterprise-owned consumer data
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: LayerFive, a cross-device identity resolution platform, is changing how enterprises leverage their own consumer data.  While consumers are interacting with an enterprise using multiple devices and channels, enterprises are leveraging only a fraction of the consumer data to improve business outcome. The problem is that enterprises are having band-aid solutions to connect identities across various data sources due to the way technology has evolved. In the digital world, the problem becomes even more acute as consumers may not always be logged in while interacting with an enterprise, and typically use multiple devices.  LayerFive's innovative AI technology resolves cross-device digital identities in a privacy-safe first party data context across both logged-in and unknown consumers. Moreover, LayerFive provides a private identity graph with identity life cycle management to ensure that an enterprise leverages the most comprehensive view of a consumer to improve business outcomes.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Software

Description: Conversational Computing Corporation doing business as Conversay, provides speech technology, interfaces, and application for mobile
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Conversational Computing Corporation doing business as Conversay, provides speech technology, interfaces, and application for mobile devices. The company specializes in embedded speech technologies. Its speech solutions enable companies to offer customers two-way access paths to data and content services. The company leverages speech engines, including Conversay Advanced Speech Software Interface, a portable and noise-tolerant speech recognition engine; Human-Quality Text-to-Speech for embedded implementations; and ISSAC, a vocabulary continuous speech recognition engine. Its technologies include JSAPI2, a speech application development standard; Conversay Master Developer Suite, a development tool enabling C/C++ programmers to build speech applications for a variety of embedded platforms; and VoiceAssist 1.0, an application suite for wireless phones, which enables speech-enabled name dialing, digit dialing, and application launch. The company also provides Conversation Forms Automation, a tool suite, which includes Conversation Forms Builder, a developer tool for describing the form elements, GUI arrangement, database dependencies, and business rules contained in a Conversationa Form; and Conversation Forms Processor(CFP), a client application that runs Conversation Forms. Its CFP's features include hands-free and eyes-free processing, and project and runtime management. The company serves wireless mobile computing market with focus on aviation and avionics, enterprise mobility, and the wireless handset/consumer electronics sectors. Conversational Computing Corporation was founded in 1992 and is based in Redmond, Washington.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Information Technology, Mobile, Software
